session.datatype
Class AbstractDatatype

java.lang.Object
  session.datatype.AbstractDatatype
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, Datatype
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractDatatypeArray, DatatypeBoolean, DatatypeByteArray, DatatypeDouble, DatatypeDoubleArray, DatatypeFactory.SimpleDatatype, DatatypeFloat, DatatypeFloatArray, DatatypeInteger, DatatypeIntegerArray, DatatypeMapEntry, DatatypeMeshElement, DatatypeObject, ElemNode, MeshNode, NumericalNeutralFileSection
public abstract class AbstractDatatype
extends java.lang.Object
implements Datatype

This abstract class provides a synchronized setContents method, which can be used by a Link implementation to provide non-blocking remote invocations. The getContents provided by this abstract class is also synchronized.

This datatype is externalized with the following format:

if (contents == null) out.writeUTF("contents.null");

else if (contents == this) out.writeUTF("contents.this");

else out.writeUTF("contents.yes"); out.writeUTF(contents.getClass().getName()); contents.writeExternal(out);

This class overrides the equals(obj) method such as it returns true if

obj == this || obj == contents || (contents != this && contents.equals(obj))

getContents

public Datatype getContents()
Description copied from interface: Datatype
It returns the object on which the methods are indeed invoked. In most cases, it is this object itself. However, when this datatype is the result of a asynchronous remote method invocation, it is another datatype object.
